RACE.RACE_TEXT: LAUREL PARK RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 83. Maiden Special Weight Purse 53860. (PLUS UP TO 15% MBF) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LEONIDS broke alertly, disputed the pace outside RUFFNER, moved away after that one checked near the three eighths, kept on under under right handed asking in mid stretch and prevailed. FULL IRISH broke inward and bumped with IRISH RILL, corrected and raced well off the early pace, eased out and gathered momentum mid turn, edged up behind a rival and stalled briefly nearing the lane, shifted in some to make progress between horses in mid stretch, altered in further and closed gamely to the inside of the winner. ASSUME NOTHING stalked the dueling leaders, advanced three wide into the stretch, gave hard chase as the closest pursuer leaving mid stretch, continued on outside the top pair but was out kicked in the final yards. GOODAFTERNOONOSCAR , urged along while saving ground, made a bit of a gain into the stretch but lacked a solid finish. MASTERWORK , sluggish from the gate, made a decent four wide run outside rivals nearing the quarter pole, drifted in some while on his left lead in upper stretch, switched over to his correct lead for the final furlong and churned on. IRISH RILL , bumped at the break, was hustled along while well back and saving ground, swung out for the drive but failed to respond. RUFFNER , fractious pre race, came away well and disputed the pace inside the winner, checked when appearing to briefly lose action near the three eighths, regrouped to chase then faltered in the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUV YA BYE BYE broke inward bumping and tightening HERE AND NOFURTHER, corrected a stride or two late and prompted the pace three deep, moved to command after a half mile, spurted clear after being set down in upper stretch, widened a bit past the eighth pole and held firm under a drive. HE ROLLS took command between rivals and set the pace in the two path, took pressure from both sides past the five sixteenths, wandered outward through the drive and gave way grudgingly. HERE AND NOFURTHER , bumped and pinched back at the break, regrouped and edged up three wide into the turn, took closer order approaching the quarter pole, shifted out in the late and closed steadily. SUPE , bumped at the break, drafted back off the early pace while off the inside, swung six wide in upper stretch and rallied. DOC ROCK prompted the pace along the inside, bid along the rail mid turn, vied into the stretch, stayed willingly while drifting a bit nearing mid stretch then faded late. ROBBEDINTHEBAHAMAS bobbled at the break, saved ground early, angled out around the turn, altered back in for the drive but lacked a rally. RIXEY ROCKET lacked speed, raced three wide into the stretch and failed to menace. NOTIMELIKEPRESENT , four deep chasing the pace, was fanned wider into the stretch and weakened through the final furlong. MR. COWBOY BRADLEY flashed speed outside foes, dropped in past the five eighths, chased and gave way. TEGO was outrun.
